🧠 Problem: Submatrices with Top-Left & Sum ≤ k
📌 Key Observation
Every valid submatrix must start from (0,0)
So submatrix is defined by bottom-right corner (i, j)

👉 That means:

We only need to check all rectangles from (0,0) to (i,j)

💡 Core Idea

Instead of checking all submatrices → fix top-left = (0,0)

So problem reduces to:

Count how many (i, j) such that
sum of rectangle (0,0) → (i,j) ≤ k

⚡ Prefix Sum Concept (2D)

We use 2D prefix sum to get sum quickly.

